Just in case no one has noticed the patch letting /ROLEplayer show on /who all GUILD commands didnt work. Any idea when this may be fixed?<P> 

<B>Erm.. That doesn't make me happy. I'll talk to the guys about it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000197.html">A couple of board bugs to fix</a></B><P>

1. The normal link to the search engine from the thread page works ok, however... the link to the "New search" while you are on a page of returned search hits is mistaken. the url is different and when you try a search using that link you never get any hits.<P>

<B>Check the "Forum/Archive" drop-down box. When you do a search inside the forum it automatically selects the "General Discussion" forum. However when you are outside the forum, it selects the first one alphabetically, which I believe is the Bertox forum.</B><P>

2. I don't have an active EQ account anymore yet here I still am, disrupting the heck out of this forum with my posts... I can tell <P>

<B>We're looking into the issue. Are you sure that you are unable to log into EverQuest? If you still had time left on your account when you cancelled, you'll be able to log in both EQ and the boards until that time expires. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000204.html">Removed Forums</a></B><P>

<I>Hello all,<P>

Some of you have noticed that we've removed some of the other forums that used to be on the board, such as "The Newbie Zone". We basically only wanted to have main forums that we knew that we could actively moderate. <P>

It does appear however that a few are missing the other forums. Please let me know here if you think that we should bring back the Newbie Zone, Theatre of the Tranquil, or the Coalition of Tradesfolk, or whether you think a forum with another focus would be appropriate.<P>

-Gordon</I><P>

I would like a humor forum, as we are no longer allowed to post that content here.<P>

<B>A humor forum might be a good idea, but I should mention that I don't see anything wrong with tasteful humor here. There's a couple of former humorous posts that I keep saved off for posterity :)</B><P>

"Post off-topic comments in threads for the purpose of drawing attention to another thread on a different subject."<P>

<B>That's for off-topic comments within existing threads. Basically this one was aimed at the "why are you addressing this issue when you should be addressing [insert issue here]" posts that seem to follow me around the threads I visit.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000206.html">Sense of Forbodding?</a></B><P>

Just an observation, but as of late, I have seen many more flames appear and more harsh responses to most posts. Seems to me that the message boards and how people are treated on these message boards is going downhill. <P>

<B>I'd like to think that we can start saying "was going downhill" in the near future rather than "is". We have great hopes that the message board changes will result in a much nicer environment for all.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000209.html">Abashi? can you please tell us if hybrid spells cost a percentage of our TOTAL mana?</a></B><P>

Thus all spells cost a flat rate which is based off of the stated amount of mana - It's a number, not a percentage.<P>

<B>Though I answered yesterday as you mentioned, probably the best way to describe spell-costs for hybrids is:<P>

Spells cast by hybrids cost their listed cost, plus a percentage of the listed cost that is inversely correlated to the level of the caster.<P>

They do not, however, cost a percentage of total mana, nor is the cost based upon total mana at the time.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000210.html">Warning about new nodrop feature.</a></B><P>

Like quite a few other EQ settings, it looks like this one gets saved through the periodic "X has saved..." feature (ex: macro buttons).<P>

I set my /fastdrop never about 2 minutes before I logged off and totally forgot about it. When I logged back in I then promptly dropped something, only to realize that my /fastdrop setting was reset back to off. That item then disappeared because of the ground terrain.<P>

So, you might want to make sure you never change your /fastdrop setting just before you log... otherwise you may assume it's one setting when it's, in fact, another.<P>

<B>The preference is stored in the global options file. It *should* be instantaneously saved to whatever you've set it at. If there's a problem with it saving, you might try deleting your .OPT files in your EverQuest directory. As a note, you'll have to reset your keys and emotes if you do that.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000216.html">VISIBLE server login names Abashi? We need to change them</a></B><P>

During the initial startup on the boards when everything was haywire, about 100 people had their server login names visible. This is a hazard if there were in fact hackers reading and scribbling madly. Please give us some sort of option to change our login names or otherwise make sure we have the security that the rest of the subscribers do.<P>

<B>I understand your concern, however as the station name is a key for the station account, it cannot be changed. I would recommend that anyone worried about the problem insure that they are using a nonsensical password comprised of letters, numbers, and no real words. In fact, the one provided by the password recovery tool would be appropriately suited to the task.<P>

If that is not sufficient for your needs, you can email our customer-service department at <a href="mailto:eqmail@verant.com">eqmail@verant.com</a> and explain the situation, they may be able to make arrangements for your concern. Many people posted on these boards routinely using their station-names in the past and we've found no correlation between them and hacked accounts.<P>

I do apologize for the short period in which station names were displayed and am certain that a password of the strength mentioned above will not be at risk. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000217.html">Positive Item Changes</a></B><P>

When I recieved my Cloak of Jaggedpine (6ac, 3dex) from Larsk Juton, he mentioned something to the effect of "Watch this cloak, as we frequently change the enchantments placed upon it." <P>

<B>When we're planning to change an item in a manner that wouldn't be announced (a positive change) it's not unusual for NPC text to indicate that something along those lines may happen. Since that text was in, I would imagine that the thoughts surrounding it's possible change may have been adjusted.</B><P>

such as switching the DEX for WIS or adding another AC, dropping a DEX so it's 7ac 2dex?)? I love finding things that aren't constant throughout the game, and I was hoping I could see this cloak do what Larsk said it would.<P>

<B>I think that most players would view any negative aspect of a change as a negative change overall, regardless the final outcome. For instance, the -1 dex that you suggest would probably get more press than the +1 ac. </B><P>

My goodness... I'm new to these boards, but that's just shocking... off the front page in close to ten minutes? That's amazing.<P>

<B>Isn't it? I've always been amazed at the number of posts here. It's nice to see this kind of passion. Welcome to the boards.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000240.html">track corpse</a></B><P>

The necromancer "Track Corpse" spell still does not work. Is there an ETA on when this may work?<P>

<B>It is on our list of current items that are being worked on, but I can't give any type of firm ETR. The spell ended up not working as envisioned, well not at all really, and it could be a few weeks more.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
